HEADWORD: Audiometer
<hw>Au`di*om"e*ter</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>audire</ets> to hear + <ets>-meter</ets>.]</ety>
<fld>(Acous.)</fld> <def>An instrument by which the power of hearing can
be gauged and recorded on a scale.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

